data.current_description: This method retrieves details on a specific seller payout. The unique identifier of the payout is passed in as a path parameter at the end of the call URI. The getPayouts method can be used to retrieve the unique identifier of a payout, or the user can check Seller Hub. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payment instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedToValue response fields in CNY value. Note: In split-payout cases, this method will only return details on an individual payout, also known as a true(actual) payoutid. If a user inputs a payoutReference id as a path parameter, the call will fail and the 404 not found status code will be returned. For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve details for a specific seller payout
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves comprehensive details for a specific seller payout using the payout ID as a path parameter. Returns payout status, amount, fees, transaction details, and payout instrument information. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), also returns payoutPercentage and CNY-converted amounts. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers. Note: Accepts only true payout IDs, not payoutReference IDs; returns 404 if payoutReference is provided.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve the details of one or more seller payouts. By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve payouts processed within a specific date range, and/or they can retrieve payouts in a specific state. There are also pagination and sort query parameters that allow users to control the payouts that are returned in the response. If no payouts match the input criteria, an empty payload is returned. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payout instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedTo response fields set to CNY value and the payoutReference, the unique identifier reference (not true payout). By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve the two true(actual) payouts associated with a payoutReference. Note: For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve multiple seller payouts with filtering
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves one or more seller payouts with support for filtering by date range and payout status, pagination, and sorting. Returns array of payout details including amounts, fees, and transaction information. Supports filtering by single payout status or date range; returns empty payload if no matches found. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), returns payoutPercentage, CNY-converted amounts, and payoutReference identifiers. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve cumulative values for payouts in a particular state, or all states. The metadata in the response includes total payouts, the total number of monetary transactions (sales, refunds, credits) associated with those payouts, and the total dollar value of all payouts. If the filter query parameter is used to filter by payout status, only one payout status value may be used. If the filter query parameter is not used to filter by a specific payout status, cumulative values for payouts in all states are returned. The user can also use the filter query parameter to specify a date range, and then only payouts that were processed within that date range are considered.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve cumulative payout summary statistics
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves aggregated payout statistics including total payout count, total monetary transaction count, and total payout value. Supports optional filtering by single payout status and/or date range. Returns cumulative values for all payout states if no status filter applied. Response includes metadata on associated sales, refunds, and credits. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method retrieves all pending funds that have not yet been distibuted through a seller payout. There are no input parameters for this method. The response payload includes available funds, funds being processed, funds on hold, and also an aggregate count of all three of these categories. If there are no funds that are pending, on hold, or being processed for the seller's account, no response payload is returned, and an http status code of 204 - No Content is returned instead.

No input parameters required. Returns 204 No Content status if no pending funds exist. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: The getTransactions method allows a seller to retrieve information about one or more of their monetary transactions. Note: For a complete list of transaction types, refer to TransactionTypeEnum. Numerous input filters are available which can be used individually or combined to refine the data that are returned. For example: SALE transactions for August 15, 2022; RETURN transactions for the month of January, 2021; Transactions currently in a transactionStatus equal to FUNDS_ON_HOLD. Refer to the filter field for additional information about each filter and its use. Pagination and sort query parameters are also provided that allow users to further control how monetary transactions are displayed in the response. If no monetary transactions match the input criteria, an http status code of 204 No Content is returned with no response payload.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve seller monetary transactions with filtering
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves one or more seller monetary transactions with support for multiple filter types (transaction type, date range, status), pagination, and sorting. Filters can be combined to refine results (e.g., SALE transactions for specific date, RETURN transactions by month, FUNDS_ON_HOLD status). Returns array of transaction details. Returns 204 No Content if no transactions match criteria. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: The getTransactionSummary method retrieves cumulative information for monetary transactions. If applicable, the number of payments with a transactionStatus equal to FUNDS_ON_HOLD and the total monetary amount of these on-hold payments are also returned. Note: For a complete list of transaction types, refer to TransactionTypeEnum. Refer to the filter field for additional information about each filter and its use. Note: Unless a transactionType filter is used to retrieve a specific type of transaction (e.g., SALE, REFUND, etc.,) the creditCount and creditAmount response fields both include order sales and seller credits information. That is, the count and value fields do not distinguish between these two types monetary transactions.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve cumulative transaction summary statistics
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves aggregated transaction statistics including transaction counts and amounts by type. Optionally returns count and amount of payments with FUNDS_ON_HOLD status. Supports filtering by transaction type and date range. Note: Without transactionType filter, creditCount and creditAmount include both order sales and seller credits combined. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method retrieves detailed information regarding a TRANSFER transaction type. A TRANSFER is a monetary transaction type that involves a seller transferring money to eBay for reimbursement of one or more charges. For example, when a seller reimburses eBay for a buyer refund. If an ID is passed into the URI that is an identifier for another transaction type, this call will return an http status code of 404 Not found.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve details for a specific transfer transaction
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves detailed information for a specific TRANSFER transaction using the transfer ID as a path parameter. TRANSFER transactions represent seller reimbursements to eBay for charges such as buyer refunds. Returns transfer details including amount, date, and associated charges. Returns 404 Not Found if the provided ID corresponds to a different transaction type. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method retrieves details on a specific seller payout. The unique identifier of the payout is passed in as a path parameter at the end of the call URI. The getPayouts method can be used to retrieve the unique identifier of a payout, or the user can check Seller Hub. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payment instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedToValue response fields in CNY value. Note: In split-payout cases, this method will only return details on an individual payout, also known as a true(actual) payoutid. If a user inputs a payoutReference id as a path parameter, the call will fail and the 404 not found status code will be returned. For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve details for a specific seller payout
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves comprehensive details for a specific seller payout using the payout ID as a path parameter. Returns payout status, amount, fees, transaction details, and payout instrument information. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), also returns payoutPercentage and CNY-converted amounts. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers. Note: Accepts only true payout IDs, not payoutReference IDs; returns 404 if payoutReference is provided.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve the details of one or more seller payouts. By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve payouts processed within a specific date range, and/or they can retrieve payouts in a specific state. There are also pagination and sort query parameters that allow users to control the payouts that are returned in the response. If no payouts match the input criteria, an empty payload is returned. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payout instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedTo response fields set to CNY value and the payoutReference, the unique identifier reference (not true payout). By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve the two true(actual) payouts associated with a payoutReference. Note: For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve multiple seller payouts with filtering
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves one or more seller payouts with support for filtering by date range and payout status, pagination, and sorting. Returns array of payout details including amounts, fees, and transaction information. Supports filtering by single payout status or date range; returns empty payload if no matches found. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), returns payoutPercentage, CNY-converted amounts, and payoutReference identifiers. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve cumulative values for payouts in a particular state, or all states. The metadata in the response includes total payouts, the total number of monetary transactions (sales, refunds, credits) associated with those payouts, and the total dollar value of all payouts. If the filter query parameter is used to filter by payout status, only one payout status value may be used. If the filter query parameter is not used to filter by a specific payout status, cumulative values for payouts in all states are returned. The user can also use the filter query parameter to specify a date range, and then only payouts that were processed within that date range are considered.

data.description_suggestion: Retrieves aggregated payout statistics including total payout count, total monetary transaction count, and total payout value. Supports optional filtering by single payout status and/or date range. Returns cumulative values for all payout states if no status filter applied. Response includes metadata on associated sales, refunds, and credits. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method retrieves all pending funds that have not yet been distibuted through a seller payout. There are no input parameters for this method. The response payload includes available funds, funds being processed, funds on hold, and also an aggregate count of all three of these categories. If there are no funds that are pending, on hold, or being processed for the seller's account, no response payload is returned, and an http status code of 204 - No Content is returned instead.

data.current_description: The getTransactions method allows a seller to retrieve information about one or more of their monetary transactions. Note: For a complete list of transaction types, refer to TransactionTypeEnum. Numerous input filters are available which can be used individually or combined to refine the data that are returned. For example: SALE transactions for August 15, 2022; RETURN transactions for the month of January, 2021; Transactions currently in a transactionStatus equal to FUNDS_ON_HOLD. Refer to the filter field for additional information about each filter and its use. Pagination and sort query parameters are also provided that allow users to further control how monetary transactions are displayed in the response. If no monetary transactions match the input criteria, an http status code of 204 No Content is returned with no response payload.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve seller monetary transactions with filtering
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves one or more seller monetary transactions with support for multiple filter types (transaction type, date range, status), pagination, and sorting. Filters can be combined to refine results (e.g., SALE transactions for specific date, RETURN transactions by month, FUNDS_ON_HOLD status). Returns array of transaction details. Returns 204 No Content if no transactions match criteria. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: The getTransactionSummary method retrieves cumulative information for monetary transactions. If applicable, the number of payments with a transactionStatus equal to FUNDS_ON_HOLD and the total monetary amount of these on-hold payments are also returned. Note: For a complete list of transaction types, refer to TransactionTypeEnum. Refer to the filter field for additional information about each filter and its use. Note: Unless a transactionType filter is used to retrieve a specific type of transaction (e.g., SALE, REFUND, etc.,) the creditCount and creditAmount response fields both include order sales and seller credits information. That is, the count and value fields do not distinguish between these two types monetary transactions.

Supports filtering by transaction type and date range. Note: Without transactionType filter, creditCount and creditAmount include both order sales and seller credits combined. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method retrieves details on a specific seller payout. The unique identifier of the payout is passed in as a path parameter at the end of the call URI. The getPayouts method can be used to retrieve the unique identifier of a payout, or the user can check Seller Hub. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payment instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedToValue response fields in CNY value. Note: In split-payout cases, this method will only return details on an individual payout, also known as a true(actual) payoutid. If a user inputs a payoutReference id as a path parameter, the call will fail and the 404 not found status code will be returned. For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve details for a specific seller payout
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves comprehensive details for a specific seller payout using the payout ID as a path parameter. Returns payout status, amount, fees, transaction details, and payout instrument information. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), also returns payoutPercentage and CNY-converted amounts. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers. Note: Accepts only true payout IDs, not payoutReference IDs; returns 404 if payoutReference is provided.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve the details of one or more seller payouts. By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve payouts processed within a specific date range, and/or they can retrieve payouts in a specific state. There are also pagination and sort query parameters that allow users to control the payouts that are returned in the response. If no payouts match the input criteria, an empty payload is returned. For split-payout cases, which are only available to sellers in mainland China, this method will return the payoutPercentage for the specified payout. This value indicates the current payout percentage allocated to a payout instrument. This method will also return the convertedToCurrency and convertedTo response fields set to CNY value and the payoutReference, the unique identifier reference (not true payout). By using the filter query parameter, users can retrieve the two true(actual) payouts associated with a payoutReference. Note: For more information on split payouts, see Mainland China Split Payout Playbook.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve multiple seller payouts with filtering
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves one or more seller payouts with support for filtering by date range and payout status, pagination, and sorting. Returns array of payout details including amounts, fees, and transaction information. Supports filtering by single payout status or date range; returns empty payload if no matches found. For split-payout cases (mainland China only), returns payoutPercentage, CNY-converted amounts, and payoutReference identifiers. Requires digital signature verification for EU/UK sellers.

data.current_description: This method is used to retrieve cumulative values for payouts in a particular state, or all states. The metadata in the response includes total payouts, the total number of monetary transactions (sales, refunds, credits) associated with those payouts, and the total dollar value of all payouts. If the filter query parameter is used to filter by payout status, only one payout status value may be used. If the filter query parameter is not used to filter by a specific payout status, cumulative values for payouts in all states are returned. The user can also use the filter query parameter to specify a date range, and then only payouts that were processed within that date range are considered.

The response payload includes available funds, funds being processed, funds on hold, and also an aggregate count of all three of these categories. If there are no funds that are pending, on hold, or being processed for the seller's account, no response payload is returned, and an http status code of 204 - No Content is returned instead.

data.current_description: The getTransactions method allows a seller to retrieve information about one or more of their monetary transactions. Note: For a complete list of transaction types, refer to TransactionTypeEnum. Numerous input filters are available which can be used individually or combined to refine the data that are returned. For example: SALE transactions for August 15, 2022; RETURN transactions for the month of January, 2021; Transactions currently in a transactionStatus equal to FUNDS_ON_HOLD. Refer to the filter field for additional information about each filter and its use. Pagination and sort query parameters are also provided that allow users to further control how monetary transactions are displayed in the response. If no monetary transactions match the input criteria, an http status code of 204 No Content is returned with no response payload.
